---

<Layout title="Chowdown" description="The macro tracker that's actually free. No, really. AI-powered food scanning with zero paywalls.">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 pt-16 md:pt-24 pb-12">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
      <span class="text-5xl">üçΩÔ∏è</span>
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-white">Chowdown</h1>
          <span class="badge-live">üü¢ Live</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-amber-400 font-medium mt-1">Free Forever Macro Tracker</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="text-xl text-gray-400 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mb-6">
      The macro tracker that's actually free. No, really. Not "free with a paywall after 3 foods." Not "free but we sell your data." <strong class="text-white">Actually free.</strong>
    </p>

    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="https://chowdown.me" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-primary">Visit chowdown.me ‚Üí</a>
      <a href="https://app.chowdown.me" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-secondary">Open the App</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 pb-16">

    <!-- The Problem -->
    <div class="prose-factory">
      <h2>The Problem</h2>
      <p>Every macro tracking app follows the same playbook: free tier with crippling limitations, then ¬£40-80/year to unlock what should be basic features.</p>
      <p>Macro tracking isn't rocket science. It's a database lookup with a nice UI. <strong>There's no reason it should cost ¬£50/year.</strong></p>
    </div>

    <!-- How It Works -->
    <div class="prose-factory mt-8">
      <h2>How It Works</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 my-6">
      {howItWorks.map(s => (
        <div class="card !p-4 relative">
          <div class="absolute top-3 right-3 text-amber-500/20 font-mono font-black text-3xl">{s.step}</div>
          <span class="text-2xl mb-2 block">{s.icon}</span>
          <h3 class="text-white font-bold text-sm mb-1">{s.title}</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-xs">{s.desc}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="prose-factory">
      <p><strong>The tech:</strong> React/Vite frontend, Firebase backend, Gemini AI for food recognition. PWA that works on any device.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Competitor Comparison -->
    <div class="prose-factory mt-8">
      <h2>The "Free Forever" Positioning</h2>
      <p>In a market where every competitor charges, being genuinely free is a statement.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto my-6">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-navy-600">
            <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-gray-400 font-medium">App</th>
            <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-gray-400 font-medium">Price</th>
            <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-gray-400 font-medium">Catch</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {competitors.map((c, i) => (
            <tr class:list={["border-b border-navy-700/50", i === competitors.length - 1 && "!bg-amber-500/5 !border-amber-500/20"]}>
              <td class:list={["py-3 px-4 font-medium", i === competitors.length - 1 ? "text-amber-400" : "text-white"]}>{c.name}</td>
              <td class:list={["py-3 px-4 font-mono", i === competitors.length - 1 ? "text-amber-400 font-bold" : "text-gray-300"]}>{c.price}</td>
              <td class:list={["py-3 px-4", i === competitors.length - 1 ? "text-green-400 font-medium" : "text-gray-400"]}>{c.limitation}</td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-factory">
      <p>It's also a viable business strategy:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>No server costs per user</strong> ‚Äî Firebase free tier is generous, AI costs are pennies per scan</li>
        <li><strong>Revenue via donations</strong> ‚Äî Buy Me a Coffee + potential B2B licensing</li>
        <li><strong>Growth through word-of-mouth</strong> ‚Äî People share things that save them money</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- B2B Angle -->
    <div class="prose-factory mt-8">
      <h2>The B2B Angle Nobody Expects</h2>
      <p>The corporate wellness market is worth <strong>¬£53 billion</strong> globally. Companies like Apple, Google, and Netflix offer health perks to employees.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card my-6 border-amber-500/20">
      <h3 class="text-amber-400 font-bold text-lg mb-4">üíº Chowdown as a Nutrition Benefit</h3>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="text-amber-400">‚Ä∫</span>
          <span class="text-gray-300">¬£1-3 per employee per month</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="text-amber-400">‚Ä∫</span>
          <span class="text-gray-300">Company dashboard with anonymised trends</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="text-amber-400">‚Ä∫</span>
          <span class="text-gray-300">Integration with existing wellness platforms</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="text-amber-400">‚Ä∫</span>
          <span class="text-gray-300">Zero friction for employees</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-4 p-3 bg-navy-900/50 rounded-lg">
        <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm font-mono">10 companies √ó 100 employees √ó ¬£2/mo = <span class="text-amber-400 font-bold">¬£24,000/year</span></p>
        <p class="text-gray-500 text-xs mt-1">Without touching the consumer product.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Content Strategy -->
    <div class="prose-factory">
      <h2>Content Strategy</h2>
      <p>The blog targets high-intent search queries, publishing 3 posts per week:</p>
    </div>

    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 my-6">
      {blogTopics.map(topic => (
        <span class="px-3 py-1.5 bg-navy-800 border border-navy-600 rounded-lg text-sm text-gray-300">"{topic}"</span>
      ))}
    </div>
    <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm">13 posts ready. Cross-posted to Dev.to and Hashnode for backlinks.</p>

    <!-- Status -->
    <div class="prose-factory mt-8">
      <h2>Current Status</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="card my-6">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3 text-sm">
        {statusItems.map(item => (
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class={item.done ? "text-green-400" : "text-gray-500"}>{item.done ? '‚úì' : '‚óã'}</span>
            <span class="text-gray-300">{item.text}</span>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- What's Next -->
    <div class="prose-factory">
      <h2>What's Next</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-3 my-6">
      {nextSteps.map((item, i) => (
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-3 bg-navy-800/40 rounded-lg">
          <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-amber-500/15 flex items-center justify-center text-amber-400 font-mono text-xs flex-shrink-0">{i + 1}</div>
          <span class="text-gray-300 text-sm">{item}</span>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="prose-factory">
      <hr />
      <p><em>Chowdown is the #2 priority in The Factory. The thesis: in a market full of paywalls, being genuinely free is the best marketing strategy there is.</em></p>
    </div>
  </div>

</Layout>
